'''Rayan Elloumi''' ({{langx|ar|ريان اللومي}}; born September 17, 2007) is a [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]] in [[Major League Soccer]]. Born in Canada, he represents the [[Tunisia national football team|Tunisia national team]].

==Early life==
Elloumi played youth soccer with Edmonton Juventus SC, before joining [[Edmonton BTB SC]] as a teenager, while spending some time in the Whitecaps FC BMO Academy Centre in Edmonton, until eventually joining the [[Vancouver Whitecaps FC Academy]] in August 2023.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.whitecapsfc.com/players/rayan-elloumi/ |title=Rayan Elloumi Whitecaps profile |work=[[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]]}}</ref><ref name=alain>{{cite web |url=https://al-ain.com/article/messi-league-jewel-tunisia-national-team |title=من دوري ميسي.. جوهرتان تبشران منتخب تونس بإنهاء أكبر الأزمات |trans-title=From Messi's league... Two gems herald Tunisia's end to its biggest crisis |language=Arabic |date=November 28, 2024 |author=محمد عماد (Mohamed Emad) |work=Al Ain}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://edmontonjournal.com/news/local-news/two-edmonton-teens-vancouver-whitecaps |title='Wow, this is really happening': Two Edmonton teens turning heads with the Vancouver Whitecaps |first=Steven |last=Sandor |date=August 11, 2025 |work=[[Edmonton Journal]]}}</ref>

==Club career==
Elloumi began playing with [[Whitecaps FC Academy]] in [[League1 British Columbia]] in 2024.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.whitecapsfc.com/news/men-s-side-begin-2024-campaign-with-1-1-draw-against-unity-fc |title=League1 BC: Men's side begin 2024 campaign with 1-1 draw against Unity FC |date=April 28, 2024 |first=Michael |last=McColl |work=[[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]]}}</ref>

On June 9, 2024, he made his professional debut with [[Whitecaps FC 2]] in [[MLS Next Pro]], in a 4–0 victory over [[Los Angeles FC 2]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.whitecapsfc.com/wfc2/news/wfc2-cruise-to-victory-over-lafc2-to-make-it-three-consecutive-wins-at-swangard |title=WFC2 cruise to victory over LAFC2 to make it three consecutive wins at Swangard! |date=June 9, 2024 |work=[[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]]}}</ref> On October 6, 2024, he scored his first goal in a 3–1 loss to [[Houston Dynamo 2]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.whitecapsfc.com/wfc2/news/playoffs-next-for-young-caps |title=Playoffs next for young 'Caps |date=October 6, 2024 |work=[[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]] |first=Felipe |last=Vallejo}}</ref> In June 2025, he signed a professional contract with Whitecaps FC 2 (after previously playing as an academy call-up).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.whitecapsfc.com/news/wfc2-sign-elloumi |title=WFC2 sign Whitecaps FC BMO Academy forward Rayan Elloumi |date=June 7, 2025 |work=[[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]]}}</ref> In June 2025, he signed a short-term loan with the [[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]] first team.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.whitecapsfc.com/news/vwfc-sign-seven-wfc2-players |title=Whitecaps FC sign seven WFC2 players to MLS short-term agreements for Sunday's match versus Seattle |date=June 8, 2025 |work=[[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]]}}</ref> He signed additional loans with the first team that month as well.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.whitecapsfc.com/news/castro-elloumi-selemani-mls-short-term-agreements |title=Whitecaps FC sign Castro, Elloumi, and Selemani from WFC2 to MLS short-term agreements for Saturday's match versus Columbus |date=June 13, 2025 |work=[[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.whitecapsfc.com/news/vwfc-sign-castro-coupland-and-elloumi-to-short-term-agreements |title=Whitecaps FC sign Castro, Coupland, and Elloumi from WFC2 to MLS short-term agreements for match against San Diego FC |date=June 25, 2025 |work=[[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]]}}</ref> He made his [[Major League Soccer]] debut on June 14, 2025, against the [[Columbus Crew]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.whitecapsfc.com/news/halfway-mark |title=Halfway mark |date=June 14, 2025 |first=Felipe |last=Vallejo |work=[[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]]}}</ref> At the end of the 2025 season, he was named the Whitecaps FC 2 player of the year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.whitecapsfc.com/news/2025-player-awards|title=Whitecaps FC announce winners for 2025 Player Awards|date=October 25, 2025|work=[[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]]}}</ref>

On September 12, 2025, Elloumi signed a [[Homegrown Player Rule (MLS)|Homegrown Player]] contract with the [[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]] through the 2028 season, with options for 2029 and 2030.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://canadiansoccerdaily.com/2025/09/12/vancouver-whitecaps-sign-forward-rayan-elloumi-to-mls-homegrown-contract/ |title=Vancouver Whitecaps sign forward Rayan Elloumi to MLS Homegrown contract |date=September 12, 2025 |work=Canadian Soccer Daily}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.whitecapsfc.com/news/vwfc-sign-bmo-academy-product-rayan-elloumi |title=Whitecaps FC sign BMO Academy product Rayan Elloumi to MLS contract |date=September 12, 2025 |work=[[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]]}}</ref> He scored his first MLS goal the following night at the age of 17 in the Whitecaps' 7–0 victory over the [[Philadelphia Union]], becoming the first Whitecaps homegrown player in club history to score on his home debut.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Vallejo |first=Felipe |date=September 14, 2025 |title=Statement made |url=https://www.whitecapsfc.com/news/statement-made |access-date=September 14, 2025 |website=[[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://onesoccer.ca/a/ali-ahmed-shines-and-rayan-elloumi-scores-1st-goal-as-whitecaps-destroy-philadelphia-union-icymi|title=Ali Ahmed shines, Rayan Elloumi scores 1st goal as Whitecaps destroy Union - ICYMI|date=September 15, 2025|first=Alexandre|last=Gangué-Ruzic|work=[[OneSoccer]]}}</ref>

==International career==
In August 2025, Elloumi was called up to the [[Canada men's national under-18 soccer team|Canada U18 team]] for a series of friendlies, although he ultimately left the camp to remain with the Whitecaps to play in league matches.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.whitecapsfc.com/news/mackenzie-elloumi-nash-canm18 |title=Mackenzie, Elloumi, Nash called up to Canada U-18 national team |date=August 25, 2025 |work=[[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]]}}</ref>

In September 2025, the [[Tunisian Football Federation]] announced that Elloumi had agreed to represent the nation at international level.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.arabesque.tn/ar/article/129568/%D8%A2%D8%AF%D9%85-%D8%BA%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%A8-%D9%88-%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%84%D9%88%D9%85%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%B9%D8%B2%D8%B2%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A8-%D8%AA%D9%88%D9%86%D8%B3-%D9%84%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%B5%D8%A7%D8%BA%D8%B1|title=آدم غلاب و ريان اللومي يعززان منتخب تونس للأصاغر|trans-title=Adam Ghallab and Rayan Elloumi strengthen the Tunisian youth team|language=ar|date=September 28, 2025|work=Arabesque|archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20251008091624/https://www.arabesque.tn/ar/article/129568/%D8%A2%D8%AF%D9%85-%D8%BA%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%A8-%D9%88-%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%84%D9%88%D9%85%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%B9%D8%B2%D8%B2%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A8-%D8%AA%D9%88%D9%86%D8%B3-%D9%84%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%B5%D8%A7%D8%BA%D8%B1|archive-date=2025-10-08}}</ref> He was called up to the [[Tunisia under-23 national football team|Tunisia U23]], where scored in his debut, a 3–0 win over [[Iraq national under-23 football team|Iraq U23]] on October 11, 2025.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jawharafm.net/ar/article/%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A8-%D8%A3%D9%82%D9%84-%D9%85%D9%86-23-%D8%B3%D9%86%D8%A9-%D9%8A%D9%81%D9%88%D8%B2-%D9%88%D8%AF%D9%8A%D8%A7-%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%89-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82/96/282837|title=منتخب أقل من 23 سنة يفوز وديا على العراق|website=JawharaFM}}</ref>

In January 2026, he was named to the [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canada senior team]] for the first time for a training camp and friendly against [[Guatemala national football team|Guatemala]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.whitecapsfc.com/news/priso-badwal-elloumi-canmnt-january|title=Priso, Badwal, Elloumi called up to Canada's men's national team for January camp|date=January 6, 2026|work=[[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]]}}</ref> He appeared in the match against Guatemala, in his first senior appearance, however, as it was designated a B-level friendly, it did not count as an official senior cap.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sportsnet.ca/soccer/article/marschs-makeshift-canadian-squad-comes-together-in-win-over-guatemala/|title=Marsch's makeshift Canadian squad comes together in win over Guatemala|date=January 18, 2026|work=[[Sportsnet]]|first=John|last=Molinaro}}</ref>

In March 2026, he was called up to the [[Tunisia national football team|Tunisia senior team]] for two friendly matches against [[Haiti national football team|Haiti]] and his country of birth, [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canada]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.whitecapsfc.com/news/rayan-elloumi-tunisia-march-window|title=Rayan Elloumi called up to Tunisia's men's national team for March international window|date=March 18, 2026|work=[[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]]}}</ref>

In May 2026, he was named to the 25 man roster for Tunisia for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, officially cap tying him to that country.

==Personal life==
Born in Canada, Elloumi is of Tunisian descent.<ref name=alain />

